properties.headline: Winter Storm Warning issued January 9 at 3:25PM PST until January 11 at 4:00AM PST by NWS Seattle WA
properties.description:
* WHAT...Heavy snow expected above 3500 feet. Total snow
accumulations of 12 to 24 inches. Winds gusting as high as 40
mph.

* WHERE...Olympic mountains and valleys, including Hurricane Ridge.

* WHEN...From 4 AM Friday to 4 AM PST Saturday.

* IMPACTS...Travel could be very difficult to impossible.

* ADDITIONAL DETAILS...The Northwest Avalanche Center expects
dangerous to very dangerous avalanche conditions Friday and
lingering through the weekend. Check nwac.us for the latest
avalanche forecast and conditions.
properties.instruction:
If you must travel, keep an extra flashlight, food, and water in
your vehicle in case of an emergency.

For the latest road conditions in Washington state, call 5 1 1.

NWSheadline: WINTER STORM WARNING IN EFFECT FROM 4 AM FRIDAY TO 4 AM PST SATURDAY ABOVE 3500 FEET
